00:10:28.168 --> 00:10:30.560
And so the business got sold
to the highest bidder, who

00:10:30.560 --> 00:10:33.580
was the bidder who cared
the least about all

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:36.380
the mission-driven things that
they did as a business, all

00:10:36.380 --> 00:10:37.900
of the culture that
they'd created,

00:10:37.900 --> 00:10:40.700
the really high standards
for manufacturing

00:10:40.700 --> 00:10:44.374
they had in developing world
markets, stuff like that,

00:10:44.374 --> 00:10:45.790
and saw all of
that stuff go away.

00:10:45.790 --> 00:10:49.590
And so for them, it was
about trying to figure out

00:10:49.590 --> 00:10:53.370
how we can help businesses
that care about something other

00:10:53.370 --> 00:10:54.470
than just making money.

00:10:54.470 --> 00:10:56.450
Entrepreneurs, people
who want to make money

00:10:56.450 --> 00:10:58.250
but do good at the same time.

00:10:58.250 --> 00:11:00.970
And for me, it
was the experience

00:11:00.970 --> 00:11:03.680
of being in the
traditional capital markets

00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:08.360
and seeing the way investors
think more and more and more

00:11:08.360 --> 00:11:11.760
short term, which
leads them to care only

00:11:11.760 --> 00:11:15.230
about making as much money in
their investments in a business

00:11:15.230 --> 00:11:17.940
as quickly as they
possibly can, and trying

00:11:17.940 --> 00:11:21.100
to externalize every
other cost on to society,

00:11:21.100 --> 00:11:22.530
all the bad stuff.

00:11:22.530 --> 00:11:24.860
And thinking that there's
got to be a different way

00:11:24.860 --> 00:11:28.517
to build a marketplace
that supports businesses

00:11:28.517 --> 00:11:30.350
so that they actually
create long-term value

00:11:30.350 --> 00:11:33.250
both for their shareholders
and their stakeholders.

00:11:33.250 --> 00:11:36.890
So that's why I
wanted to start B Lab.

00:11:36.890 --> 00:11:39.922
A lot more interesting
