much beauty and food,

00:38:27.230 --> 00:38:31.230
and we don't think about
hunger on a daily basis.

00:38:31.230 --> 00:38:33.630
I know it's not necessarily
at the forefront of my mind

00:38:33.630 --> 00:38:36.430
as I'm passing by a
microkitchen stocked with food.

00:38:36.430 --> 00:38:38.840
What are some ways
that you think

00:38:38.840 --> 00:38:41.150
young people such as ourselves
that work at companies

00:38:41.150 --> 00:38:45.660
like Google can contribute to
the B Corporation community,

00:38:45.660 --> 00:38:48.940
to B Lab, to B Corporations,
small businesses,

00:38:48.940 --> 00:38:53.292
or even to just promote
knowledge around the community?

00:38:53.292 --> 00:38:54.250
I'll start with Anjali.

00:38:54.250 --> 00:38:56.740
ANJALI KUMAR: I think
there's a lot of ways.

00:38:56.740 --> 00:38:59.290
I think starting with being
a conscious consumer, that's

00:38:59.290 --> 00:39:00.580
always a great place to start.

00:39:00.580 --> 00:39:03.080
That's a really easy way to
start, voting with your dollars

00:39:03.080 --> 00:39:06.520
and spending money at companies
that share that value system

00:39:06.520 --> 00:39:08.460
if that's something
that you hold dear.

00:39:08.460 --> 00:39:10.967
And I would think an audience
full Googlers, that there's

00:39:10.967 --> 00:39:13.550
a reason that you're here, and
it's beyond just the free food.

00:39:13.550 --> 00:39:16.469
It's really because of the core
value system of this company.

00:39:16.469 --> 00:39:18.010
It's certainly why
I was here and why

00:39:18.010 --> 00:39:20.450
I was really proud to
be here for so long.

00:39:20.450 --> 00:39:23.330
So I think starting with
that is a great way.

00:39:23.330 --> 00:39:26.220
I was thinking a little bit
more about your question

00:39:26.220 --> 00:39:28.240
about what I would
want from Googlers

00:39:28.240 --> 00:39:30.720
and what my ask would be.

00:39:30.720 --> 00:39:32.600
And it's not really
a technology ask.

00:39:32.600 --> 00:39:35.020
It's more like a "help
me solve this problem"

00:39:35.020 --> 00:39:37.902
ask, which is, you think
about the number of people

00:39:37.902 --> 00:39:39.860
in the world that don't
have access to glasses.

00:39:39.860 --> 00:39:41.540
It's a billion people, right?

00:39:41.540 --> 00:39:44.470
That's like a full 15%
of the world's population

00:39:44.470 --> 00:39:47.820
that does not have access
to prescription eyewear that

00:39:47.820 --> 00:39:48.670
need it.

00:39:48.670 --> 00:39:50.771
And that's a staggering
statistic, right?

00:39:50.771 --> 00:39:52.270
And that's a
distribution challenge.

00:39:52.270 --> 00:39:54.520
If we could actually get
classes into the hands of all

00:39:54.520 --> 00:39:57.420
those people who need it, they
could increase their earning

00:39:57.420 --> 00:39:59.210
potential by 20%.

00:39:59.210 --> 00:40:01.250
What a low-cost poverty
alleviation tool.

00:40:01.250 --> 00:40:02.875
We don't need to give
them information,

00:40:02.875 --> 00:40:04.874
we don't need to give
them all this other stuff.

00:40:04.874 --> 00:40:06.490
We can, but let's
start with glasses.

00:40:06.490 --> 00:40:09.510
It's a really simple tool to
help people change their lives

00:40:09.510 --> 00:40:11.630
in a really meaningful way.

00:40:11.630 --> 00:40:13.330
And again, it's a
distribution problem.

00:40:13.330 --> 00:40:15.288
I can't get glasses into
all these folks' hands

00:40:15.288 --> 00:40:17.220
because I can't get to them.

00:40:17.220 --> 00:40:18.420
Help me figure that out.

00:40:18.420 --> 00:40:19.820
That would be amazing.

00:40:19.820 --> 00:40:21.850
Let's get glasses to everybody.

00:40:21.850 --> 00:40:24.660
So if somebody
here wants to help

00:40:24.660 --> 00:40:26.610
me think about
those problems, that

00:40:26.610 --> 00:40:29.590
would be amazing, and help
me find those partners of how

00:40:29.590 --> 00:40:32.720
we do this in a responsible
way, in a sustainable way,

00:40:32.720 --> 00:40:36.024
not just in pure charity
and just giving them away

00:40:36.024 --> 00:40:37.940
and disrupting local
economies and businesses.

00:40:37.940 --> 00:40:41.590
But really creating a
sustainable solution

00:40:41.590 --> 00:40:42.780
to that problem.

00:40:42.780 --> 00:40:44.090
That would be incredible.

00:40:44.090 --> 00:40:47.690
And so I think that's sort of my
big ask, but in a smaller way,

00:40:47.690 --> 00:40:50.393
I think it's just start with
where you spend your money.

00:40:50.393 --> 00:40:53.340
MIKE BRADY: Could I add
